In PyCharm, go to "File" > "Settings" (or "PyCharm" > "Preferences" on macOS).
In the left pane, navigate to "Python Integrated Tools" and select "Pytest."
In the right pane, specify the following:


pytest --rA --html=Reports\Reports.html TestCases/test_Email_Transcription.py::TestCases/test_End_the_session_from_user_side.py::TestCases/test_Sessions_getting_logged_or_Not.py


Python Markers:
@pytest.mark.smoke has 2
@pytest.mark.optional has 1
@pytest.mark.regression  has 3
#command to use markers, m stands for marker

            pytest -m smoke
            pytest -m optional
            pytest -clearm regression
